{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:psalms.74",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 74,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 74 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:1",
      "text": "A Psalm of instruction for Asaph. - Wherefore hast thou rejected us, O God, for ever? wherefore is thy wrath kindled against the sheep of thy pasture?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:2",
      "text": "Remember thy congregation which thou hast purchased from the beginning; thou didst ransom the rod of thine inheritance; this mount Sion wherein thou hast dwelt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:3",
      "text": "Lift up thine hands against their pride continually; because of all that the enemy has done wickedly in thy holy places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:4",
      "text": "And they that hate thee have boasted in the midst of thy feast; they have set up their standards for signs,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:5",
      "text": "ignorantly as it were in the entrance above;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:6",
      "text": "they cut down its doors at once with axes as in a wood of trees; they have broken it down with hatchet and stone cutter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:7",
      "text": "They have burnt thy sanctuary with fire to the ground; they have profaned the habitation of thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:8",
      "text": "They have said in their heart, even all their kindred together, Come, let us abolish the feasts of the Lord from the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:9",
      "text": "We have not seen our signs; there is no longer a prophet; and God will not know us any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:10",
      "text": "How long, O God, shall the enemy reproach? shall the enemy provoke thy name forever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:11",
      "text": "Wherefore turnest thou away thine hand, and thy right hand from the midst of thy bosom for ever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:12",
      "text": "But God is our King of old; he has wrought salvation in the midst of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:13",
      "text": "Thou didst establish the sea, in thy might, thou didst break to pieces the heads of the dragons in the water.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:14",
      "text": "Thou didst break to pieces the heads of the dragon; thou didst give him for meat to the Ethiopian nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:15",
      "text": "Thou didst cleave fountains and torrents; thou driedst up mighty rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:16",
      "text": "The day is thine, and the night is thine; thou hast prepared the sun and the moon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:17",
      "text": "Thou hast made all the borders of the earth; thou hast made summer and spring.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:18",
      "text": "Remember this thy creation: an enemy has reproached the Lord, and a foolish people has provoked thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:19",
      "text": "Deliver not to the wild beasts a soul that gives praise to thee: forget not for ever the souls of thy poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:20",
      "text": "Look upon thy covenant: for the dark places of the earth are filled with the habitations of iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:21",
      "text": "let not the afflicted and shamed one be rejected: the poor and needy shall praise thy name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:22",
      "text": "Arise, O God, plead thy cause: remember thy reproaches that come from the foolish one all the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.74.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 74,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 74:23",
      "text": "Forget not the voice of thy suppliants: let the pride of them that hate thee continually ascend before thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
